The paper deals with resource allocation and interference management in a cognitive ad hoc network, which involves information theory (cs.IT), networking (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.MM), control systems (cs.SY), and possibly machine learning (cs.AI) techniques. The use of beamforming and feedback mechanisms also suggests a focus on wireless communication (cs.IT, cs.NI).
